Class DynamicEnum

java.lang.Object
com.dua3.license.DynamicEnum
public final class DynamicEnum extends Object
A class that provides a dynamic, runtime-defined enum-like functionality. This allows for defining a set of enumerated values at runtime, as opposed to traditional Java enums which are defined at compile time.

  • Method Details

    • ofNames

      public static DynamicEnum ofNames(String... names)
      Creates a new instance of DynamicEnum with the specified names. Each name will correspond to a unique value in the DynamicEnum, and must be non-duplicate.
      Parameters:
      names - the names of the dynamically defined enum values. Each name must be unique.
      Returns:
      a new DynamicEnum instance containing the provided enum names as values.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if any duplicate names are provided or a name does map to an invalid enum name

    • ofNamesAndValues

      public static DynamicEnum ofNamesAndValues(String[] names, String[] values)
      Creates a new instance of DynamicEnum using the specified names and values. Each name will correspond to a unique value, and both names and values must have the same length.
      Parameters:
      names - an array of Strings representing the enum names. Each name must be unique.
      values - an array of Strings representing the corresponding enum values.
      Returns:
      a new DynamicEnum instance containing the provided names and values.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the lengths of names and values do not match, if duplicates exist in names, or if names contain invalid enum names.

    • fromProperties

      public static DynamicEnum fromProperties(Properties properties)
      Creates a new instance of DynamicEnum from a Java Properties instance. The property names will be used as the enum names and values.
      Parameters:
      properties - the Properties instance containing the enum names
      Returns:
      a new DynamicEnum instance containing the property names as enum names and values
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the Properties instance is empty, contains duplicate names, or contains names that map to invalid enum names

    • fromPropertiesWithValues

      public static DynamicEnum fromPropertiesWithValues(Properties properties)
      Creates a new instance of DynamicEnum from a Java Properties instance. The property names will be used as the enum names and the property values will be used as the enum values.
      Parameters:
      properties - the Properties instance containing the enum names and values
      Returns:
      a new DynamicEnum instance containing the property names as enum names and property values as enum values
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the Properties instance is empty, contains duplicate names, or contains names that map to invalid enum names

    • values

      public DynamicEnum.EnumValue[] values()
      Retrieves an array containing all the enum-like values defined in this DynamicEnum instance. The returned array is a copy and modifications to it will not affect the original data.
      Returns:
      an array of DynamicEnum.EnumValue instances representing the values of this DynamicEnum

    • valueOf

      public DynamicEnum.EnumValue valueOf(String name)
      Retrieves an EnumValue object from the dynamic enum based on its name.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the desired EnumValue; must be a non-null, case-sensitive string matching the name of an existing EnumValue
      Returns:
      the EnumValue corresponding to the specified name
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the provided name does not match any existing EnumValue in the dynamic enum
